article.headline: New Orleans 84, Tulane 77
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Bo McCalebb scored 27 points and grabbed 13 rebounds as New Orleans beat Tulane 84-77 on Monday. Jamie McNeilly scored 16 points and James Parlow added 15 points and 10 rebounds for UNO (7-7). The Privateers shot just 40 percent from the floor but hit 56 percent of their 3-point shots (9-of-16). UNO committed just six turnovers. David Gomez led Tulane (7-5) with 32 points on 9-of-13 shooting. He was 14-of-17 from the free throw line and grabbed 10 rebounds. Robinson Louisme had 13 points while Chris Moore had 12 for the Green Wave. McCalebb scored 15 points in the first half and helped UNO grab a 31-22 lead with 4:19 left. Tulane then held UNO without a field goal for the last 2:38 and trailed 34-30 at halftime. Tulane went on a 10-0 run starting at the 16:54 mark of the second half and held a 44-41 lead with 15:09 left. But UNO held Tulane to just three field goals during an eight-minute stretch of the game's final 10 minutes.
